{"type":"message","id":"e4fd6935","parentId":"eb737a08","timestamp":"2026-04-03T12:06:21.883Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Interpreting Workspace Skills**\n\nI'm now focusing on the user's intent: identifying skills located inside the current workspace directory. My interpretation of \"into Workspace\" is \"within\" the `/app/skills/` directory. I'm cross-referencing this understanding with the initial list of available skills to generate a focused response.\n\n\n**Clarifying Workspace Scope**\n\nI'm now grappling with the user's implicit intent, considering if they mean skills *available to* the workspace versus skills *located inside* it. The initial interpretation focused on `/app/skills/`, but the phrasing \"into Workspace\" suggests a more literal location within the user's project directory. The initial list doesn't match the current directory, so I must clarify if they want skills in the workspace's project directory.\n\n\n"},{"type":"text","text":"<final>The skills I listed previously are the ones currently available to me, and they are located in the `/app/skills/` directory, which is part of my core OpenClaw installation.\n\nIf you're asking about skills specifically located *within* the `/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/` directory (your project workspace), I don't see any listed in my available skills that are under that specific path.\n\nCould you clarify if you meant skills that are *available to* me (which I've already listed) or skills that are physically located in *your current workspace directory*?</final>","textSignature":""}],"api":"google-generative-ai","provider":"google","model":"gemini-2.5-flash","usage":{"input":1547,"output":374,"cacheRead":19330,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21251,"cost":{"input":0.0004641,"output":0.0009350000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0014497499999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00284885}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775217978456,"responseId":"O63PaY7vMJSUnsEPg9rbkQ8"}